               <msContents>
                  <summary>1r: legal document concerning a quittance of debt, dated 1140 of the
                     Seleucid Era (= 1129 CE) and written under the authority of Maṣliaḥ ha-Kohen.
                     Mentions Abū l-Maʿālī b. Joseph (known as Ibn Tamar) and Yešuʿa b. Ḥananya.
                     Signed by Ḥalfon b. Manasseh and Nathan ha-Kohen b. Solomon. 1v: will of Kulla
                     b. Šabbat, mentioning Judah Ibn al-Sofer, the daughter of Kulla’s brother Abū
                     ʿAlī al-Kohen and Yešuʿa ha-Kohen b. ʿEli. In the hand of Ḥalfon b. Manasseh.
                     2r: legal document concerning a quittance of debt, dated 1446 (= 1135 CE) and
                     signed by Ḥalfon b. Manasseh and Elʿazar b. Joseph. Mentions Jacob Abū l-Maʿālī
                     b. Joseph, known as Ibn Kujik (כוגך, Kushek, Persian 'Small') and Abū ʿAlī b. Samuel b. Solomon
                     (known as Ibn al-Dustarī). 2v: legal document concerning the illegitimate
                     descendance of Abū Saʿd, son of al-Wuḥša the broker, mentioning Abū ʿAlī
                     al-Parnas Yefet b. Maṣliaḥ, Ibn al-Sukrī, Ḥalfon ha-Kohen b. Joseph and Abū
                     Naṣr al-Kohen Ibn al-Kamūḵī. </summary>
